<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Transport for London (TfL) is warning of traffic disruption along the A406 northbound, Gunnersbury Avenue, for the next three days.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>
<p>This is due to urgent works by Thames Water to repair a burst water main.</p>
<p>The works will take place between Chiswick Roundabout and Gunnersbury Lane, with a complete closure of the northbound section.</p>
<p>Diversions are in place and drivers are advised to find alternative routes and allow extra time for their journey.</p>
<p>Thames Water has advised that they will do everything possible to clear the road of works by Saturday 7 June.</p>
<p>For more detail on the road closures, and for up to date information on traffic in London, call the TfL traffic line on 020 7222 1234, log on to <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/tfl/livetravelnews/realtime/tube/default.html">Traffic News</a> or tune into Traffic Radio on DAB digital radio.</p>

     

        
        
        
